```
func CreateStackedEtcdStaticPodManifestFile(client clientset.Interface, manifestDir, patchesDir string, nodeName string, cfg *kubeadmapi.ClusterConfiguration, endpoint *kubeadmapi.APIEndpoint, isDryRun bool, certificatesDir string) error {
	etcdPeerAddress := etcdutil.GetPeerURL(endpoint)
...
klog.V(1).Infof("[etcd] Adding etcd member: %s", etcdPeerAddress)
		cluster, err = etcdClient.AddMemberAsLearner(nodeName, etcdPeerAddress) 

```


`AddMemberAsLearner` is called which after adding the new learner member updates will call
```
	// Add the new member client address to the list of endpoints
	c.Endpoints = append(c.Endpoints, GetClientURLByIP(parsedPeerAddrs.Hostname()))

	return ret, nil
}
```

From this point onwards the learner member is contained in the client `c.Endpoints` member

And later when we call `err = etcdClient.MemberPromote(learnerID)` we instantiate a new etcd client using this list of endpoints
```
	klog.V(1).Infof("[etcd] Promoting a learner as a voting member: %s", strconv.FormatUint(learnerID, 16))
	cli, err := c.newEtcdClient(c.Endpoints)
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}
```

From my cloud init logs error it then seems like some of the calls to `c.isLearner(learnerID)` are being sent to the learner member rather than the existing full member. The log line seems to indicate that full member is the one being queried
```
"target":"etcd-endpoints://0xc000a3cb40/xxx.xxx.xxx.131:2379"
```

I should also note that the environment im testing in was experiencing some connectivity issues so I am not concerned with why the promote failed initally, in it the original etcd node was having issues connecting to the new learner node

So my questions are
1. Is my analysis correct? i.e. once a learner member is added it becomes eligable as an endpoint for future etcd queries by kubeadm
2. If it is should there be some extra handling added to the client to prevent it from using the learner endpoint until it has been promoted
3. If analysis is wrong why do I get an error of `etcdserver: rpc not supported for learner` from a full member

